* Iron sighed, shaking her head and finally FINALLY clearing it.
So instead of anger, sadness, she discovered that she was fine.
< Mood swing.>
Well, come to think of it she had had some pains in her stomach a night or 
two ago but she also hadn't eaten anything in the longest of time.
But she had been mean and she looked over her shoulder at Prowl with a sorry 
look on her face.
< I'm sorry, things are just getting to me.>
But then she turned her eyes back towards the field, the evening closing in 
and orange light spilling onto the , black siluets fighting.
Even though she had began to hate battle, the sight was rather 
beautiful...if you forgot the sounds of gunshots and battle cries.
She almost seemed lost in the sight for a few moments, arm hanging limp at 
her side, her eye looking dark and far away.
But she answered Prowl, none the less.*

" Yes, take them all in and make sure they're regenerated."
